          div.subhead-01 WIREFRAMES
          div.margin-top-sm Campaign headquarters liked the direction of the recovery-themed maps, which used data about the stimulus bill. The first wireframes showed stimulus projects color-coded by category. These categories corresponded to the campaign’s core policy areas: education, energy, health and infrastructure. Since most of the data was uncategorized, we mobilized volunteers to label about 2,000 projects. 

          div.margin-top-sm Once we had some sample data to work with, the engineers and I started writing code. We planned to have a simple prototype running in a week. Things were moving along. So far, so good.

      div.row.margin-top-medium
